comment:
I think domestic abuse is one of the worst crimes. Not because the physical damage is the most serious, but rather because your partner is supposed to be the one who stands at your side doing all they can to help you. It's a betrayal. Accusing someone of doing it if they haven't is disgusting. No outsiders know the truth. I just feel it's telling that none of Depp's former wives or girlfriends have stood up for Heard. If you've abused one partner, you've likely abused another. You'd expect at least one of the previous women in his life to speak our or at least keep quiet. Instead they've come out to speak out on his behalf, not simply passively ignoring the whole affair but actively speaking out to support him. On top of that, people who have spoken out in his support include Heard's parents! This is one of the biggest tells for me. Why on earth would a couple speak out on behalf of someone who hit their daughter on multiple occasions? It beggars belief. They've even claimed that she has done similar before. 

I've always been proud of the British legal system, as it seems fair, everyone being allowed to have legal representation & the evidence being central to the case, but I am ashamed this time. The original judge claimed that Depp's argument that she was only making the accusation because of the financial rewards during the divorce was unfounded because she had donated the 7 million to charity. If there is proof she didn't do this, or even a suspicion that can be investigated, the case should be reopened. The judge has refused this. I am disgusted. Heard has potentially committed perjury, yet the judge does not seem concerned. Either the full picture has not been made public or there has been a miscarriage of justice. That is unacceptable.
